videos.title: What to Do When First Tower Falls
videos.desc: Former LCS Pro Lattman gives us eye opening insight into the correct macro choices you must make once claiming the first tower in the bot lane. We analyzed a bunch of korean pro players and low elo players to contrast for this one! MUST WATCH!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Balancing Farming and Ganking in the Early Game
videos.desc: We review games submitted by subscribers just like you trying to balance ganking and farming. Find out what they did wrong, right, and the most common mistakes and how to avoid them.

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Farming in the Mid Game
videos.desc: Our saviour Lattman is here to once again save our low elo subscribers from the tragedy of missing TONS of CS in the mid-late game as an ADC. Watch this to get your CS numbers up!

videos.title: SubScriber Breakdown: Pushing as a Melee!
videos.desc: We review games submitted by subscribers! In this one, we went over pushing the lane as a melee, come learn what went well and what did not!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Stop Being Afriad to Trade!
videos.desc: We reviewed some games sent in by our subscribers and told them not to be scared to trade. We had a lot of great gameplay sent in and learned a lot!

videos.title: How to Balance Farming and Ganking like Peanut
videos.desc: Learn the art of balancing farming and ganking from the veteran jungler Peanut.

videos.title: Stop Sucking at Farming After Lane Phase
videos.desc: In this guide, we highlight why most players suck at farming after lane phase and what your role should be to significantly increase your CS numbers!

videos.title: An Alternative Way To Play a Melee vs Ranged Matchup
videos.desc: Most of the time you let the wave push into you as a melee champ in top lane, but sometimes you should push. This video explains when and why!

videos.title: Low Elo Mistakes: Jensen Smurfing in Diamond
videos.desc: We found a game of jensen playing on his smurf. Then we broke it down so you can understand why he stomped this lissandra as cassio!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Avoiding the Second Buff Gank Timing
videos.desc: In this guide, we analyse how low elo players do when trying to avoid the enemy jungler's very common 'second buff gank timing'. Enjoy!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Starting the Same Side as the Enemy Jungler
videos.desc: We review games submitted by subscribers just like you starting on the same side as the enemy jungler. Find out what they did wrong, right, and how to avoid the common mistakes.

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Extended Trades
videos.desc: Our subscribers sent in some gameplay with the goal of trying extended trades. In this video we break down how they did!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Stacking Big Waves
videos.desc: Our subscribers sent in some gameplay of them trying to stack big waves. Come see what went right or wrong!

videos.title: Breaking Down Ruler's Wave Control
videos.desc: Lattman unlocks the secrets behind world champion Ruler's immaculate wave control techniques that take everything to a higher level. Not recommended for beginners!

videos.title: How to Counter Gank like Jankos
videos.desc: Starting on the same side of the map as the enemy jungler means you'll end up clashing with them on the opposite side. Learn how you can use this to your advantage and the basics of counter ganking.

videos.title: How NOT to play Melee vs Ranged
videos.desc: Playing melee vs ranged in top lane can be really simple if you learn the right trading patterns. This video demonstrates that using gameplay from Lourlo on Camille!

videos.title: How Challengers Set up their Lane to Punish Melee Champions
videos.desc: Learn how to bully melee champions as a ranged one in this video!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Not Falling Behind When Pushed
videos.desc: Our former LCS pro Lattman soothes the pain our Skill-Capped subscribers feel when getting pushed into their tower in the bot lane. Learn to deal with getting pushed without falling behind and everything in between!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Tracking the Enemy Jungler!
videos.desc: N/A

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Pushing as Ranged
videos.desc: We sent our subscribers to push as as a ranged champion in top lane, come watch what went right or wrong.

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Forcing Bad Recalls
videos.desc: Our subscribers sent in some gameplay of themselves trying to force bad recalls, watch how they did in this video!

videos.title: How Doublelift Deals with a High Kill Threat Lane
videos.desc: Team Liquid's Doublelift is a master of the lane phase. Luckily Lattman is here to break down how Doublelift is able to shrug off high kill threat lanes seemingly very easily!

videos.title: Tracking the Enemy Jungler At a High Level
videos.desc: Learn everything a jungler should know about how to track the enemy jungler. Watching this video is the equivalent of downloading maphacks.

videos.title: Destroying Players that Bring Ignite
videos.desc: Tired of losing to ignite top? In this video we show you how to deal with that and use it against them.

videos.title: How Faker Used Wave Control to Force a Terrible Recall
videos.desc: Forcing the enemy to take a bad recall can win you the lane. In this video we learn how Faker does it!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Staying Healthy Without Falling Behind
videos.desc: We sent our subscribers out to try and apply pure fundamentals to their trades. Then we broke it down so you can learn!

videos.title: Strategy Breakdown: Playing Around Ranged Minions
videos.desc: Lattman is here to run us through exactly how you want to play around ranged minions in the lane phase to gain large trading advantages you wouldn't otherwise be able to obtain. A core fundamental of trading!

videos.title: Strategy Breakdown: Harassing when they go for CS
videos.desc: One of the first things you learn about raned vs melee is harassing when they go for CS. Our subscribers tried it and this is how it went!

videos.title: Setup The Lane to Smash Champs AND Towers!
videos.desc: In this video you will learn how to not only get kills, but towers as well!

videos.title: Winning On a Simple Champ with No Mechanics
videos.desc: Sometimes play easy champions can let you focus more on macro. In this video we show a perfect example of this!

videos.title: Subscriber Breakdown: Executing Burst Trades
videos.desc: We sent our subscribers to try burst and extended trades, come see how it went so you can learn!

videos.title: Using Burst/Extended Trades vs Oppresive Laners
videos.desc: Two types of trades are most common, burst, and extended. Come see when to use each one and why!

videos.title: Strategy Breakdown: Executing the Predator Route
videos.desc: We analyze real players just like you and see what they did wrong when executing the Korean Predator Route.

videos.title: The Predator Route Sweeping Korean Challenger
videos.desc: We cover a new route sweeping Korean Challenger that involves getting early boots to activate your Predator Rune.

videos.title: How Doublelift Crushes a Losing Lane
videos.desc: In this guide we run you through how Team Liquid's Doublelift can crush lane even when he's playing the losing matchup by abusing some key fundamental trading concepts that you can EASILY apply to your own games!

videos.title: Strategy Breakdown: Trying to Freeze with Reset Advantage
videos.desc: In this guide, Lattman sheds some insight on WHEN and HOW you want to freeze in low elo with a winning goal in mind and all of the problems that may come along the way and how to avoid them!

videos.title: Zven's Intelligent Wave Control with Harass Timings
videos.desc: TSM Zven's highly intelligent wave control is able to negate any lane threat while also identifying key trading windows to obtain large health leads. Learn how!

videos.title: Landing Meaningful Harass Without Losing CS
videos.desc: In this video we break down the  best way to play ranged vs melee so you dont miss CS and get a lot of harass as well!

videos.title: Strategy Breakdown: Getting Picks in Your Own Games
videos.desc: Our subscribers went and applied the knowledge they learned from the assassin macro video in their own games! Come see what went right and wrong!

videos.title: Mid Lane Macro as an Assassin
videos.desc: Carrying games as an assassin can be hard. In this video, you will learn the macro to make it easier.

videos.title: The Three Wave Gank Strategy
videos.desc: TSM Bjergsen uses the three wave gank strategy to pressure his opponent at the start of the lane and then setup a brutal freeze to crush lane phase while practicing in Korea.

videos.title: Teamfighting Part 3: Doublelift's Tristana
videos.desc: In this teamfight guide series, we run you through how to unlock the purpose of your role: being an attack damage carry. This requires high damage per second output and is most valuable in teamfights. This is where you should shine and is why you should study ALL of our teamfighting guides for ADCs!
